definitions.definition: A flying insect , of the clade Anthophila within the hymenopteran superfamily Apoidea , known for its organised societies (though only a minority have them), for collecting pollen and (in some species) producing wax and honey .
( informal , proscribed ) Any stinging flying insect, especially a wasp .

main_definition: A flying insect , of the clade Anthophila within the hymenopteran superfamily Apoidea , known for its organised societies (though only a minority have them), for collecting pollen and (in some species) producing wax and honey .
secondary_definitions: ( informal , proscribed ) Any stinging flying insect, especially a wasp .

definitions.definition: A contest , especially for spelling ; see spelling bee .
A community gathering to share labour, e.g. a sewing bee or a quilting bee.
